title: Andrew Eyapan
content:
Andrew Ekai Eyapan (born December 12, 1965) is a long-distance runner from Kenya, who won the 1998 edition of the Vienna Marathon. He is a former race walker, who won the bronze medal in the men's 20Â km Walk at the 1990 African Championships in Cairo, Egypt. He won the Berlin Half Marathon in 1998.
